  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package intentionally carries an orphan claim (no prov:wasDerivedFrom) and validation results with no uncertainty quantification, triggering W-EP-01 (Critical) and W-AL-01 (High) simultaneously on the same UnitOfAssurance, which in turn triggers COMPOUND-01.",
